    Run the Macro F1 Test Pipeline

    test.MacroF1.Rd

    This function orchestrates the full pipeline for testing the Macro F1 metric in a multi-label classification setting. It sequentially executes the partitioning, evaluation, and organization of results, while recording execution times.

    test.MacroF1(parameters)

    Arguments

    parameters

    A list containing the configuration settings, including paths for data storage and the dataset name.

    Value

    The function does not return a value but generates evaluation results and a CSV file summarizing execution times.

    Details

    The function executes the following steps:

    • Building partitions: Calls maf1.test.build().

    • Gathering predictions: Calls maf1.test.gather.predicts().

    • Evaluating folds: Calls maf1.test.evaluate().

    • Gathering evaluations: Calls maf1.test.gather.evaluated().

    • Organizing evaluations: Calls maf1.test.organize.evaluation().

    • Saving runtime data: Stores execution times in a CSV file.

    Examples

    if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{
parameters <- list(
  Number.Folds = 10,
  Dataset.Name = "sample_dataset",
  Folders = list(
    folderTestSilho = "~/data/Test-Silho"
  )
)
test.MacroF1(parameters)
} # }
